      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="group border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
            How far in advance should I start planning my relocation?
            <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform"></i>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">
            Ideally 2–3 months before your move date. Visa processing alone can take 2–8 weeks depending on the country. Starting early gives you time for document apostille, housing research, and proper notice to your current employer.
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
            What documents do I need to relocate abroad for work?
            <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform"></i>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">
            Common documents include: valid passport, signed employment contract, university degree (often apostilled), birth certificate, health insurance proof, passport photos, and proof of accommodation. Requirements vary by country.
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
            Do I need to register my address when moving to a new country?
            <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform"></i>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">
            Yes, most countries require address registration within days or weeks of arrival. In Germany it's Anmeldung (within 14 days), in the Netherlands you register at the municipality to get your BSN, and in Sweden you register with Skatteverket for your personnummer.
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
            Should I open a local bank account before or after moving?
            <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform"></i>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">
            It's recommended to have an international-friendly account (like Wise or Revolut) before moving, and then open a local bank account within the first week of arrival. You'll typically need your address registration and ID to open a local account.
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-4 cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
            What is the Anmeldung in Germany?
            <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform"></i>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">
            Anmeldung is the mandatory address registration in Germany. You must register at the local Bürgeramt within 14 days of moving in. You'll need your passport, rental contract, and a landlord confirmation form (Wohnungsgeberbestätigung). This is required for almost everything else—bank accounts, tax ID, insurance.
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
